    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/7662001c482d63e1119aafcebc0e13d1201a2805/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/util.lua#L1369-L1370\n\n... causes window width to be clipped inside the window spawning the float instead of the entire screen. This is fine for `relative = 'cursor'` or `relative = 'mouse'`, but is incorrect for `relative = 'editor'`.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. `:vsplit`\n2. Open a file that can produce diagnostics\n3. Write bad code to produce a diagnostic\n4. Hover cursor over bad code\n5. `:lua vim.diagnostic.open_float({ relative = 'editor', width = vim.o.columns, max_width = vim.o.columns, offset_x = 0, offset_y = vim.o.lines, border = 'single', })`\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nI expect the float to be full screen width instead of (in the repro) half width.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.12.2\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nDebian\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nAlacritty\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nappimage",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
